{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-08T09:50:00Z", "url": "https://anfieldindex.com/80779/salah-playing-way-out-of-ballon-dor-contention.html", "publishedAt": "2025-04-08T09:50:00Z", "content": "Liverpools Wobble at Craven Cottage Raises Late-Season Questions\r\nFulham Exploit a Faltering Defence\r\nLiverpools commanding run of form hit a major roadblock at Craven Cottage, with a 3-2 defeat to F… [+2964 chars]", "title": "Salah Playing Way Out Of BalLon d’Or Contention", "fullContent": "Liverpool’s commanding run of form hit a major roadblock at Craven Cottage, with a 3-2 defeat to Fulham that raised more than eyebrows—it raised concerns. This was their third loss in four matches across all competitions and arguably their poorest defensive display of the season. The champions-elect, who had gone 26 Premier League games unbeaten, looked nothing like title winners against Marco Silva’s side.\nAs The Telegraph reported, “The champions-elect are the best team in the land but they certainly did not look like it here, against an aggressive and organised Fulham, as their 26-game unbeaten league run came to an end.”\nQuestions are now emerging over the once-dependable core of Arne Slot’s Liverpool. “Some of the certainties of Liverpool’s season – an immaculate Virgil van Dijk, for example, or a decisive Mohamed Salah – are seemingly no longer guaranteed.” Van Dijk struggled mightily against Fulham’s Rodrigo Muniz, and Salah’s drought extended to seven club games without a goal from open play.\nAlex Iwobi, full of invention and spark, “outshone here by Fulham’s Alex Iwobi,” added insult to injury for the Merseysiders.\nLiverpool’s early lead via a sublime individual strike from Alexis Mac Allister was a mere flash of hope. What followed was 14 minutes of defensive collapse. “Those 14 minutes were remarkable in their defensive incompetence, with Curtis Jones and Andy Robertson both at fault and Van Dijk totally beaten by Muniz.”\nThat tailspin stunned the visitors. While the second-half revival, capped by a goal from Luis Díaz, showed promise, the inconsistency was too much. As The Telegraph put it: “If they keep playing like they did in the first half, they might not win again this season.”\nFulham’s attacking trio—Ryan Sessegnon, Iwobi, and Muniz—delivered both substance and style. Behind them, centre-back Calvin Bassey was immense. His second-half display matched the fervour of Craven Cottage, where “the home supporters could not help but match his energy.”\nMarco Silva’s side, now pushing for European qualification, earned every inch of this result through structure, intensity, and belief.\nThere’s no escaping it—this wasn’t a blip, it was a blueprint for how to beat Liverpool. Slot’s side looked fractured in the first half, not just defensively but in terms of mentality. That three-goal blitz wasn’t about bad luck; it was about a lack of composure and organisation. For Van Dijk to be so handily beaten by Muniz is unthinkable a few seasons ago. And Salah’s goalless streak? It’s turning into a serious issue at the worst possible time.\nYes, the league cushion remains healthy, but this is a momentum game. One slip becomes two, and suddenly it’s a title race again. If the first-half version of this team shows up again, fans will start to question whether Slot has instilled enough resilience. The second half was encouraging—but we’ve seen this pattern before. Fix the defending or face an anxious run-in.\n\nสล็อตเว็บตรง\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \nsister casino sites\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\nCopyright © 2009-2025 AnfieldIndex.com . All Rights Reserved."}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-08T05:50:00Z", "url": "https://anfieldindex.com/80774/david-ornstein-confirms-major-virgil-van-dijk-contract-news-as-liverpool-talks-progress.html", "publishedAt": "2025-04-08T05:50:00Z", "content": "In the realms of football, where uncertainty often looms like an uninvited guest, the news of Virgil van Dijk’s potential contract extension with Liverpool brings a sense of relief and anticipation. … [+2934 chars]", "title": "David Ornstein Confirms Major Virgil Van Dijk Contract News as Liverpool Talks ‘Progress’", "fullContent": "In the realms of football, where uncertainty often looms like an uninvited guest, the news of Virgil van Dijk’s potential contract extension with Liverpool brings a sense of relief and anticipation. David Ornstein, speaking to NBC, sheds light on what appears to be a promising horizon for the Dutch defender at Liverpool. Ornstein’s insights echo a sentiment of optimism, suggesting that it’s a matter of “when” rather than “if” van Dijk will renew his commitment to the Reds. As he states, “The negotiations have been positive and cordial,” highlighting the smooth nature of discussions between the player and the club.\nAt 33, Virgil van Dijk remains a pillar of strength and reliability for Liverpool. His role is crucial under manager Arne Slot, and his performances consistently reflect his importance. The fact that he has not missed a minute of Liverpool’s Premier League campaign this season is a testament to his fitness and dedication. This level of consistency is rare and invaluable, particularly in a league as demanding as the Premier League. With Liverpool conceding only 30 goals in 31 matches, van Dijk’s leadership at the back is undeniable.\nThe heart of Liverpool’s defence, van Dijk, revealed progress in his contract talks following a match. “There is progress, yeah,” he confirmed, expressing his affection for the club and its supporters. His words, “I love the club, I love the fans,” resonate with the mutual appreciation between the player and the Liverpool faithful. It’s this bond that often tips the scales in favour of long-term commitments between players and their clubs.\nIn conjunction with van Dijk’s news, Liverpool also seems poised to secure Mohamed Salah’s future. Ornstein’s commentary extends beyond just van Dijk, indicating a similar positive trajectory in negotiations with Salah. This strategic move to secure key players underscores Liverpool’s intentions to maintain their core squad, ensuring stability and continuity.\nThe news of Virgil van Dijk’s contract negotiations moving in a positive direction is exactly what we need after a period of uncertainty. His unwavering presence and performance level make him indispensable to the team’s structure and aspirations. The thought of him continuing at Anfield is not just comforting; it’s exhilarating.\nMoreover, the potential simultaneous renewal of Mohamed Salah’s contract could be the catalyst needed for Liverpool to push for greater achievements. With Arne Slot at the helm, securing the backbone of our squad signifies a commitment to a prosperous era ahead. It’s about building on the foundation laid by legends and steering towards a future filled with triumphs.\nIn conclusion, the developments around van Dijk’s contract, as well as Salah’s, paint a picture of a club that’s not just reacting to changes but strategically planning for a competitive edge. As fans, we can look forward to more moments of brilliance, more matches won, and hopefully, more titles at Anfield.\n\nสล็อตเว็บตรง\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \nsister casino sites\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\nCopyright © 2009-2025 AnfieldIndex.com . All Rights Reserved."}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-08T15:50:00Z", "url": "https://anfieldindex.com/80791/liverpool-were-given-golden-ticket-this-season-former-red-on-clubs-fortunate-premier-league-title-pursuit.html", "publishedAt": "2025-04-08T15:50:00Z", "content": "When Arne Slot took over the reins at Liverpool, succeeding Jurgen Klopp, expectations were mixed. The task was monumental: evolving a team that had seen its fair share of glory under Klopp into a fr… [+3683 chars]", "title": "“Liverpool Were Given Golden Ticket This Season” – Former Red on Club’s ‘Fortunate’ Premier League Title Pursuit", "fullContent": "When Arne Slot took over the reins at Liverpool, succeeding Jurgen Klopp, expectations were mixed. The task was monumental: evolving a team that had seen its fair share of glory under Klopp into a fresh, dominant force. Slot, previously with Feyenoord, has not only met but surpassed these expectations, steering Liverpool to the top of the Premier League with an impressive lead. Harry Kewell, speaking to Sky Sports News, emphasized how Slot’s strategy has been integral in this transformation.\n“Fantastic, I don’t think he could have wished for a better opportunity,” Kewell remarked, noting how the Premier League landscape this season provided a prime opportunity for Slot. The decline in form of major rivals like Arsenal and Manchester City created an opening that Liverpool expertly exploited.\n\nA key factor in Liverpool’s success this season, as Kewell pointed out, has been the unexpected drop-off in performance from their closest rivals. Arsenal and Manchester City, who were neck-and-neck in the previous season, have faced significant challenges. Arsenal’s season was marred by crucial injuries, while City seemed to struggle with an identity crisis, leading to their worst campaign in recent years.\n“It’s harsh for what I’m about to say, but it’s kinda help that Arsenal have had a terrible time, City have had a terrible time, Chelsea have not 